fiestas are related to one another in very special ways involving both religious practices and their respective pre-Hispanic origins. A mixture of secular and sacred, patron saint fiestas are multi-day affairs that include many events, ritual specialists, and performers, with the participation of the entire community. Fiestas take place in order to honor the saints, and they are the occasion for religious ceremonies, processions, musical performances, dances, and dance dramas. They feature spectacular costumes, enormous puppets, masked and cross-dressed individuals, dazzling fireworks, rodeos, food stands, competitions, and public dances. By encompassing all of these events and performances, this work displays the essence of Mexico, a lens through which this country's complex history, religion, ethnic mix, traditions, and magic can be viewed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aChichimeca-Jonaz IndianszMexicozSan Luis de la PazxReligion. 0aChichimeca-Jonaz IndianszMexicozSan Luis de la PazxSocial life and customs. 0aChristian patron saintszMexicozSan Luis de la Paz. 0aChristian patron saintszMexicozSan Miguel de Allende. 0aFasts and feastszMexicozSan Luis de la Paz. 0aFasts and feastszMexicozSan Miguel de Allende. 0aHoly WeekzMexicozSan Miguel de Allende. 0aOtomi IndianszMexicozSan Miguel de AllendexReligion. 0aOtomi IndianszMexicozSan Miguel de AllendexSocial life and customs. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aSherzer, Dina, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSherzer, Joel, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292793460423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292793460/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA